    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="488"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d488">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.5111 European Co-operation/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation to the General
                        Disarmament Conference (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from"
                            >Gibson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-14T23:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1932—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 14—7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>331. Supplementing my 329, July 14, 8 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1"
                        >Simon</persName> issued two statements here to journalists which were
                    issued at the same time in London and which you have doubtless received through
                    press. I quote his letter to <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>
                    transmitting copies: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“My Dear <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>: I think you may
                            like to see the two statements issued in London an hour ago correcting
                            any misunderstanding about <list>
                                <label>1.</label>
                                <item>The declaration made yesterday in London and Paris and</item>
                                <label>2.</label>
                                <item>The “Gentlemen’s Agreement”.<note n="45" xml:id="d488fn45">See
                                        telegram No. 225, July 14, 5 p.m., from the Ambassador in
                                        Great Britain, <ref target="#pg_690">p. 690</ref>.</note>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <p>This completely clears up the misunderstanding about <persName
                                corresp="#p_CAN1">Chamberlain</persName> and you will be glad to
                            note that the language you suggested has been employed. I am very much
                            obliged to you.</p>
                        <p>I repeated the same explanations to the journalists here and added (again
                            following your suggestion) that the declaration made yesterday is an
                            invitation to European powers to adopt as an internal continental rule
                            the mode of open and candid discussion. I emphasized that it is neither
                            the creation of a European bloc against anybody nor the creation of an
                            Anglo-French compact against anybody.</p>
                        <p>Yours very truly,</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">John Simon</persName>”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
